a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, apron, welding gloves and face shield, etc.; 
b) Fire-fighting equipment to be on stand-by - Portable extinguishers, fire hose, etc.; 
c) Freshly welded or cut parts are not to be touched; 
d) Regular checks should be carried out on completion.

a) The Manufacturer's Manual must be consulted for procedures etc., prior to any maintenance or repairs being carried out; 
b) Only qualified person(s) may operate the equipment; 
c) All equipment must be inspected and tested - machines, cables, hoses, electrodes, etc.; 
d) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, apron, welding gloves and face shield, etc.

