a) The Manufacturer's Manual must be consulted for procedures, etc., prior to any maintenance or repairs being carried out; 
b) A plan must be agreed and approved by the Master prior to starting any work concerning installation or removal of temporary lashing points / fixings for the purpose of securing cargo or other equipment; 
c) Permission must be obtained from Master and/or Chief Engineer for any hot work; 
d) Safe Work Permit to be issued; 
e) Crew involved in the task to be briefed; 
f) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, apron, welding gloves and face shield, etc.; 
g) Combustible materials must be removed from the working area and adjacent compartment, were possible; 
h) Isolate the deck below and around the hot work area, including gaps in tweendecks. Close all hatches and/or install screens where necessary; 
i) Particular care must be taken on the position of fuel tanks; 
j) Remove or protect any cables or other items that may be affected by heat; 
k) Consult 'Enclosed Space Entry' Risk Assessment, where applicable; 
l) Fire-fighting equipment to be on stand-by - Portable extinguisher, fire hose, etc.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, apron, welding gloves and face shield, etc.; 
b) All equipment to be connected correctly and checked for earthing, etc.; 
c) All deck areas and surfaces in the vicinity of welding to be kept dry; 
d) When welding on deck, ballasting/de-ballasting operations and washing on deck is not permitted; 
e) When precipitation occurs, welding to be suspended, tools collected and placed in a dry place.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, apron, welding gloves and face shield, etc.; 
b) Working area to be thoroughly ventilated. Use fixed or portable fans if required; 
c) Rest should be taken at suitable intervals; 
d) Looking at the arc without a face shield should be avoided.
